321    /**
322    * Creates a pie chart with default settings that compares 2 datasets.
323    * The colour of each section will be determined by the move from the value
324    * for the same key in <code>previousDataset</code>. ie if value1 > value2
325    * then the section will be in green (unless <code>greenForIncrease</code>
326    * is <code>false</code>, in which case it would be <code>red</code>).
327    * Each section can have a shade of red or green as the difference can be
328    * tailored between 0% (black) and percentDiffForMaxScale% (bright
329    * red/green).
330    * <p>
331    * For instance if <code>percentDiffForMaxScale</code> is 10 (10%), a
332    * difference of 5% will have a half shade of red/green, a difference of
333    * 10% or more will have a maximum shade/brightness of red/green.
334    * <P>

346    * percentDiffForMaxScale indicate the change
347    * required to reach top scale.
348    * @param greenForIncrease an increase since previousDataset will be
